body: Great. Just make sure you pass the `start` timestamp. Otherwise you are requesting too much data (you'll have duplicates) See maybe what david did here: https://github.com/marionleborgne/sensor-data-app/blob/master/ui/chart.js#L7-L30

Hey @nicolasochem , I think you will still want to use `subprocess.Popen` not `subprocess.call`. It allows you to use the `.communicate()`. I don't think that method works with `subprocess.call`.

```
muse_process = subprocess.Popen(cmd, stdout=subprocess.PIPE)
muse_process.communicate()
```
